1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:02,110
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:03,640
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:05,110
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:12,080
(Episode 17)

5
00:00:15,850 --> 00:00:16,990
Oh, no!

6
00:00:19,190 --> 00:00:20,190
Are you okay?

7
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:21,960
Seriously?

8
00:00:22,730 --> 00:00:24,000
My hand slipped.

9
00:00:25,830 --> 00:00:26,830
I'm so sorry.

10
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,000
It's fine.

11
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,470
But your shoes are
completely soaked.

12
00:00:35,510 --> 00:00:36,510
Are you going to keep them on?

13
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,450
You should probably take them off.

14
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:45,080
Unless...

15
00:00:46,550 --> 00:00:48,620
there's a reason
you can't take them off?

16
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:19,780
Did Choi Yu Na just...

17
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:25,390
It may be uncomfortable,
but if you're okay, let's head in.

18
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:28,230
Right. I'll escort you
to your office.

19
00:01:28,330 --> 00:01:29,390
What are you talking about?

20
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,700
If they're uncomfortable,
she should take them off.

21
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,000
Here, let me help you.

22
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:47,750
Adele is a very strange company.

23
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:51,750
You're making me take my shoes off
on my very first day.

24
00:02:11,470 --> 00:02:12,640
There's no scar.

25
00:02:13,770 --> 00:02:16,980
So, she isn't Baek Jin Ju after all?

26
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:25,520
Since it's an old scar,

27
00:02:25,850 --> 00:02:27,920
it will require several rounds
of treatment.

28
00:02:28,290 --> 00:02:31,360
It'll be as painful
as it is difficult.

29
00:02:31,890 --> 00:02:33,090
This scar...

30
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:37,130
meant something special to me.

31
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:41,600
How could I, your father,
let you get a burn like that?

32
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:45,500
Even now, my heart breaks
whenever I see that scar.

33
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,640
Come on, this scar is the reason
you got back on your feet.

34
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:55,250
After Mom...

35
00:02:55,810 --> 00:02:57,650
passed away,

36
00:02:58,580 --> 00:03:00,920
you would just lie in bed all day,
staring at the ceiling.

37
00:03:01,820 --> 00:03:03,560
But when I scalded myself
with hot water,

38
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,090
you jumped out of bed
and found your strength again.

39
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:12,300
So every time I look at this scar,

40
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:15,170
I'm grateful, because it feels like
it brought my dad back to me.

41
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:23,740
The pain of peeling off my skin?

42
00:03:26,610 --> 00:03:28,580
I can endure any amount of it.

43
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:35,350
The pain of losing my dad,

44
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:39,320
or of letting go...

45
00:03:40,260 --> 00:03:42,590
of my precious memories with him?

46
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,560
Compared to that pain,

47
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:51,700
this is nothing.

48
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:03,850
Chloe.

49
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:16,760
Right. There's no way
Baek Jin Ju is alive.

50
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:20,160
If she's really just Chloe,

51
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:23,170
I don't have anything
to fear anymore.

52
00:04:33,850 --> 00:04:35,480
(Jewelry Division,
Director Kim Myung Hui)

53
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:36,980
Isn't it so weird?

54
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:40,850
Yu Na had Chloe take off her shoes
to check her bare feet.

55
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,020
Then Yu Na ran straight
to the chairman's office.

56
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:44,590
What about Chloe?

57
00:04:44,590 --> 00:04:46,390
She headed to her office,
carrying her shoes.

58
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,060
Where are you going?

59
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:54,130
You've got a big interview today.

60
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,370
Director, where are you going?

61
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:06,240
Chloe doesn't have this scar
on her foot.

62
00:05:06,710 --> 00:05:08,650
I just confirmed it myself.

63
00:05:09,980 --> 00:05:14,550
Doesn't this prove
that Chloe isn't Baek Jin Ju?

64
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:16,590
This one measly scar?

65
00:05:18,020 --> 00:05:21,790
You can always get a scar removed
if you really want to.

66
00:05:22,730 --> 00:05:24,560
Baek Jin Ju is definitely dead.

67
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,860
What are you trying to confirm?

68
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:30,470
You're sure she's dead?

69
00:05:34,770 --> 00:05:38,440
So I wouldn't have to order a hit
on someone already dead...

70
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:44,680
or hold anyone accountable
for botching the job?

71
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:48,690
Is that what you're telling me?

72
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,720
Of course.

73
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:54,460
Baek Jin Ju is most certainly dead.

74
00:06:03,170 --> 00:06:06,840
Bring me something more conclusive
than a useless photo.

75
00:06:08,170 --> 00:06:12,110
I want proof
that can't be erased or manipulated.

76
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:25,760
I picked a pair that suits you.

77
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:28,260
Glamorous and stunning.

78
00:06:28,530 --> 00:06:30,660
Just your style.

79
00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:32,260
Thank you.

80
00:06:38,140 --> 00:06:40,610
It's your first day,
so you'll have a lot to do.

81
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:42,610
So...

82
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,680
Thank you.

83
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:50,010
Go ahead and pick a pair.

84
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:58,890
I knew it.

85
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,960
See? I told you
these were more her style.

86
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:12,740
What's wrong?

87
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,510
Are they too small?

88
00:07:21,850 --> 00:07:23,950
Try them on. I'm sure they'll fit.

89
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:48,440
Seems like I have the same shoe size
as that dead woman.

90
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:52,280
But clearly,
our styles are worlds apart.

91
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:54,250
This design is awful.

92
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:20,870
What do you two think you're doing?

93
00:08:21,510 --> 00:08:22,870
What is it this time?

94
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,580
She...

95
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,480
isn't Baek Jin Ju.

96
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:31,420
Stop treating her like she is,
giving her shoes and stuff.

97
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:34,390
You look at Chloe
and think of Jin Ju, too.

98
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:39,560
That's why you took off her shoe
to see if she had the scar.

99
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:42,290
A scar?

100
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:45,660
Baek Jin Ju had a scar on her foot?

101
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,430
I didn't see one on Chloe's.

102
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,500
Exactly. You could see
she didn't have a scar.

103
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,070
Chloe...

104
00:08:54,610 --> 00:08:56,570
is clearly not Baek Jin Ju.

105
00:09:02,410 --> 00:09:04,780
You saw she had no scar,
so just get over it!

106
00:09:07,990 --> 00:09:10,820
There's no scar,
but her shoe size matches.

107
00:09:11,020 --> 00:09:12,690
So...

108
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:16,390
we can't be sure yet.

109
00:09:18,030 --> 00:09:22,330
The fact that she has no scar
proves that Chloe is just Chloe.

110
00:09:22,970 --> 00:09:23,970
Right?

111
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:25,770
Why do you care so much?

112
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:28,210
Because I need her to be Chloe
and no one else.

113
00:09:29,210 --> 00:09:30,270
Only then...

114
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:32,780
can I pursue her
without any hesitation.

115
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:34,680
What are you talking about?

116
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:38,220
It means I'm betting
that Chloe isn't Baek Jin Ju.

117
00:09:40,180 --> 00:09:41,690
And one more thing.

118
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:44,520
You only get to mess with Chloe
just this once.

119
00:09:45,820 --> 00:09:47,930
This is your one and only warning.

120
00:09:50,730 --> 00:09:52,730
First, it was all about Baek Jin Ju,

121
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:54,730
and now it's all about Chloe.

122
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:58,670
All right.

123
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,200
Fine.

124
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,840
Like Chairman Park said,

125
00:10:03,870 --> 00:10:05,880
I'll get definitive proof....

126
00:10:06,540 --> 00:10:07,750
and prove it to them.

127
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:29,530
Yes, it's me.

128
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:33,600
They're already going crazy
trying to verify me on my first day.

129
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,710
We need to hit back quickly.

130
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:39,080
I'll proceed as planned.

131
00:10:58,430 --> 00:10:59,630
What brings you by?

132
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:02,770
I won't beat around the bush.

133
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:07,100
I saw you and Chloe
in the outdoor lounge yesterday.

134
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:10,440
It didn't seem like something
I could just let slide.

135
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:14,510
I want to hear it from you directly.
Will you tell me?

136
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,550
If by any chance...

137
00:11:20,820 --> 00:11:22,620
you have feelings for her...

138
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:23,620
Mother.

139
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:31,260
Please, just give me some time.

140
00:11:31,330 --> 00:11:34,270
I'll tell you once I know for sure.

141
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,730
Once you know for sure?

142
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:41,670
Are you looking for an answer
from Chloe too?

143
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:44,980
Ms. Choi seemed to be trying
to confirm something as well.

144
00:11:47,810 --> 00:11:49,180
I'll ask this one thing.

145
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,950
Are all these situations
involving Chloe...

146
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:56,790
going to affect...

147
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:59,490
our bio division's rebranding?

148
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:05,800
Is the company's business
all you care about?

149
00:12:05,930 --> 00:12:09,600
When you and everyone else
won't give me a straight answer,

150
00:12:09,830 --> 00:12:11,540
I can't just wait around forever.

151
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:15,140
The bio division must succeed,

152
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:16,710
and our rebranding plans...

153
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:18,110
Then do what you have to do.

154
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:23,610
Chloe and I won't get in the way
of your plans.

155
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,290
I'm sure you're busy,

156
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:33,920
so you should go.

157
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,370
You should know...

158
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:48,070
I'm much more worried
about you than work.

159
00:12:48,910 --> 00:12:50,010
You say you're worried,

160
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:52,310
but you still want to go ahead
with your plan.

161
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:54,410
Every time I'm reminded of that,

162
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:57,820
it just makes me uncomfortable.

163
00:13:07,090 --> 00:13:08,290
I thought...

164
00:13:09,260 --> 00:13:11,530
we were starting to get closer,

165
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:13,730
but here we are again.

166
00:13:31,850 --> 00:13:33,350
(Division 1 Director's Office)

167
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:42,390
Director Kim.

168
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,100
Ms. Kim,

169
00:13:46,530 --> 00:13:48,930
you'd better come see this.

170
00:13:57,940 --> 00:13:59,010
This way.

171
00:14:06,350 --> 00:14:08,320
You have an interview
with a business magazine today,

172
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:11,420
but it looks like Chloe's team
brought in another film crew.

173
00:14:11,490 --> 00:14:14,860
It turns out Chloe
will be filming a documentary,

174
00:14:15,290 --> 00:14:17,030
so we'd appreciate your cooperation.

175
00:14:20,970 --> 00:14:23,200
Here comes Chloe now.

176
00:14:33,710 --> 00:14:36,410
It's your first day,
so perhaps you've made a mistake.

177
00:14:36,850 --> 00:14:40,320
If you were planning a shoot,
you should've cleared it first.

178
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:43,450
Isn't our schedule too tight
to argue about protocol?

179
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:48,330
We were rushing to meet
Adele's rebranding deadline.

180
00:14:48,990 --> 00:14:51,730
With the new logo reveal,
the new product launch,

181
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,060
and the additional ad campaign
coming up,

182
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:58,570
this shoot
is absolutely essential today.

183
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:03,010
This shoot had to be today.
Right, Dad?

184
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:04,740
Yes.

185
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:07,340
I thought you were her agent.

186
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:11,480
When Chloe was still a mystery,

187
00:15:11,680 --> 00:15:15,050
revealing myself as her father
would have exposed her.

188
00:15:15,050 --> 00:15:18,020
So I posed as her agent
to protect and support her.

189
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:20,260
But now that she has debuted,

190
00:15:20,260 --> 00:15:24,430
I'll appear in this documentary
as her father.

191
00:15:34,570 --> 00:15:38,040
But if you think
following procedure matters more,

192
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,810
I can adjust
the entire rebranding schedule.

193
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:42,950
We can do everything else
by the book...

194
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:45,350
and take our time with it.

195
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:49,020
So, what will it be?

196
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:54,430
Very well.
Just be as discreet as possible.

197
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:59,000
I'll do my best.

198
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:03,870
All right, let's get to it.

199
00:16:07,970 --> 00:16:09,070
Shall we?

200
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:15,580
Is this it?

201
00:16:16,310 --> 00:16:18,020
This is the jacket
Kim Myung Hui hung up...

202
00:16:18,020 --> 00:16:19,050
after following Tae Ho in.

203
00:16:20,350 --> 00:16:23,220
I can't have anything she's touched
in my closet.

204
00:16:26,020 --> 00:16:27,960
Mrs. Ok!

205
00:16:28,990 --> 00:16:30,090
Yes, ma'am.

206
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,560
What on earth?

207
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:33,560
Were you just waiting
outside my door?

208
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:35,930
This just arrived from the company.

209
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:39,040
It's the weekly trend report
from Director Seo.

210
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:43,310
How would you know
this is the weekly report?

211
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,810
Have you been reading my mail?

212
00:16:46,410 --> 00:16:49,080
Please. Why would I need to?

213
00:16:49,410 --> 00:16:50,710
You always...

214
00:16:50,710 --> 00:16:53,620
call Director Seo to chew him out
as soon as you read it.

215
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:58,260
By the way, why is
the chairman's jacket on the floor?

216
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:01,930
Kim Myung Hui touched it,
so send it to the dry cleaners.

217
00:17:02,330 --> 00:17:04,800
On second thought,
just throw it out.

218
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:08,530
Darn it.

219
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,780
That tramp Kim Myung Hui is doing
a business magazine interview?

220
00:17:27,350 --> 00:17:28,920
She's not even officially
the president,

221
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:29,920
but she acts like
she owns the place.

222
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:37,860
It's me.

223
00:17:38,230 --> 00:17:41,170
Why did you report the interview
and stop there?

224
00:17:41,370 --> 00:17:43,400
You should've told me your plan
to stop the interview...

225
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,400
and prevent her
from becoming president.

226
00:17:45,970 --> 00:17:47,600
This is no way to get things done.

227
00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:50,810
Gather everyone. Now!

228
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:55,710
Honestly,
none of them can do anything right.

229
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:59,750
You've got one right here
who can get the job done.

230
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:02,720
You're the biggest failure of all.

231
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,690
You haven't even looked at
what I brought you.

232
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:06,920
I've got the real deal this time.

233
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:10,660
These are the families
you'd want as in-laws.

234
00:18:12,630 --> 00:18:14,000
No matter what,

235
00:18:14,430 --> 00:18:16,330
Hyun Jun must marry into a family
that's better than Yu Na's.

236
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:17,430
Of course.

237
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,900
I found a list of women
who would be kind...

238
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:22,210
and a good fit for Hyun Jun.

239
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:25,640
This is what you call respectable?

240
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:28,610
Her wealth
is basically pocket change.

241
00:18:28,610 --> 00:18:30,710
This concerns
your only son's marriage.

242
00:18:30,780 --> 00:18:33,720
You should be looking at the person,
not their portfolio.

243
00:18:33,780 --> 00:18:35,920
Their portfolio defines
who they are.

244
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:39,160
They must be helpful to Hyun Jun.
That's what makes them respectable.

245
00:18:39,490 --> 00:18:43,960
I can't let our Hyun Jun marry
for strategy.

246
00:18:44,530 --> 00:18:47,430
There you go again.
Stop saying "our Hyun Jun."

247
00:18:48,570 --> 00:18:51,170
Mind your own business
and get ready to leave.

248
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:04,150
As you all know,
we plan to rebrand the bio division.

249
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:08,550
Once the new logo is chosen
and the new product is launched,

250
00:19:08,650 --> 00:19:10,890
we'll need to run
an additional PR campaign.

251
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:14,530
I think my upcoming documentary
could really help with that.

252
00:19:14,930 --> 00:19:17,590
So I'll need
everyone's full cooperation.

253
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,460
Ready, Dad?

254
00:19:23,730 --> 00:19:26,540
Hello, everyone. I'm Chloe's father.

255
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:29,240
Her dad?

256
00:19:30,770 --> 00:19:32,440
So he's not her agent...

257
00:19:33,980 --> 00:19:35,410
You're Chloe's father?

258
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:42,220
Nice to meet you.

259
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,260
A pleasure.

260
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:50,830
Nice to meet you.

261
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,260
Hello there.

262
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:56,830
I hope we get along.

263
00:20:01,970 --> 00:20:03,440
I'm Park Hyun Jun, Father.

264
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:06,780
Hold on. Wait, that actually hurts.

265
00:20:06,780 --> 00:20:07,810
Sorry about that.

266
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:09,580
That's quite the grip.

267
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:14,020
Father, I was wondering
why your daughter is so stunning,

268
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,720
and now I see she takes after you.

269
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:18,420
Her dad?

270
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:20,390
So Chloe is...

271
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:22,630
that man's daughter?

272
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:23,930
Hyung Jun, is it?

273
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:28,400
- Actually, it's Hyun Jun.
- Right, Park Hyun Jun.

274
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,770
- That's right.
- Can you let go now?

275
00:20:30,770 --> 00:20:32,900
- Right.
- You have clammy hands.

276
00:20:32,970 --> 00:20:35,770
Not only are you fashionable,
but you're tall too.

277
00:20:35,770 --> 00:20:37,540
Everything about you is stylish.

278
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:41,910
- Here.
- Thanks.

279
00:20:47,420 --> 00:20:49,250
Did the shoot go well?

280
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,990
Sure! Of course.

281
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:57,590
It's not like it will ever air,
but I said to make it convincing.

282
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:00,030
The final scene is
especially important to us,

283
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:01,670
so they'll do a good job.

284
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:04,530
It'll be the show's highlight.

285
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:13,370
I sealed them in separate envelopes,
just like you said.

286
00:22:14,470 --> 00:22:15,710
If I bring them in like this,

287
00:22:16,110 --> 00:22:17,710
can I get the results immediately?

288
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,780
Once again, he looks troubled.

289
00:22:29,190 --> 00:22:33,060
It's been years
since I've seen that kid smile.

290
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:35,330
Hello.

291
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:36,960
Hey.

292
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:39,860
So this is where you were.

293
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:46,800
Look at the head
of the bio division slacking off.

294
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:50,040
If you slack off too,

295
00:22:50,170 --> 00:22:51,240
who'll do the work around here?

296
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:53,440
What about the shoot?

297
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:56,180
Looks like they're pretty much done.

298
00:22:58,450 --> 00:23:02,190
When Chloe and her father
were side by side in the same shot,

299
00:23:04,590 --> 00:23:05,890
you could see a subtle resemblance.

300
00:23:10,130 --> 00:23:11,130
What now?

301
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:15,200
And now for the highlight
of the day.

302
00:23:15,570 --> 00:23:17,870
We'll take
the final group shot together.

303
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,200
Please gather at...

304
00:23:20,670 --> 00:23:21,740
Isn't this...

305
00:23:24,670 --> 00:23:27,040
Hey, wait up!

306
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:32,850
- Excuse me.
- You can't barge in like this.

307
00:23:32,850 --> 00:23:35,320
May I see the chairman?
It won't take long.

308
00:23:35,390 --> 00:23:37,190
- There he is.
- Chairman Park.

309
00:23:37,850 --> 00:23:40,890
Please approve this in support
of the bio division's success.

310
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:43,630
I'm sure you're fine
with a quick on-camera interview.

311
00:23:54,270 --> 00:23:58,680
The film crew asked
why I joined the Adele Group,

312
00:23:59,340 --> 00:24:02,350
and I told them it was because
I'm interested in Temi Bio.

313
00:24:03,410 --> 00:24:04,580
Temi Bio?

314
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:08,620
And when it comes to Temi Bio,

315
00:24:08,690 --> 00:24:12,220
I figured you'd be
the best person to ask.

316
00:24:32,510 --> 00:24:34,010
Great work, everyone.

317
00:24:34,950 --> 00:24:38,150
Will you run the story
as soon as she's named president?

318
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:39,950
Of course. Don't worry.

319
00:24:40,350 --> 00:24:41,550
Thank you for your time today.

320
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:43,590
Thanks, everyone. Get home safe.

321
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:47,990
Next on the schedule is...

322
00:24:47,990 --> 00:24:48,990
Chloe did what?

323
00:24:49,590 --> 00:24:52,600
What on earth?
In the chairman's office?

324
00:24:56,270 --> 00:24:58,540
But we're the ones
who approved this shoot.

325
00:24:58,970 --> 00:25:00,440
If this blows back on us...

326
00:25:05,980 --> 00:25:07,210
Good grief.

327
00:25:14,850 --> 00:25:18,960
People are wondering
why I chose Adele Group.

328
00:25:19,860 --> 00:25:23,360
But I'm wondering
why the Adele Group...

329
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:25,700
chose Temi Bio.

330
00:25:39,540 --> 00:25:41,680
As I reflected on my dad's death,

331
00:25:42,380 --> 00:25:43,380
the true intentions...

332
00:25:44,380 --> 00:25:47,320
of Choi Yu Na and her father,
Choi Sam Sik, became clear.

333
00:25:50,390 --> 00:25:51,390
But...

334
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:56,460
I have no idea
what Chairman Park was trying to do.

335
00:25:57,360 --> 00:26:00,000
He ruthlessly took over Temi Bio...

336
00:26:01,430 --> 00:26:02,700
and then just sat on it.

337
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:08,540
If I can figure out
why Park Tae Ho targeted Temi Bio...

338
00:26:09,540 --> 00:26:11,070
and what he really wanted,

339
00:26:12,510 --> 00:26:16,550
I can drive a wedge
between him and Choi Yu Na.

340
00:26:22,450 --> 00:26:23,590
In that case,

341
00:26:24,790 --> 00:26:26,890
we need to create a situation
where you can ask,

342
00:26:27,160 --> 00:26:30,130
and Chairman Park has no choice
but to answer.

343
00:26:31,730 --> 00:26:32,730
Any ideas?

344
00:26:37,730 --> 00:26:40,800
That's it. I've got an idea.

345
00:27:00,320 --> 00:27:01,520
Temi Bio...

346
00:27:04,630 --> 00:27:05,830
was a mistake on my part.

347
00:27:07,930 --> 00:27:09,200
A mistake?

348
00:27:09,830 --> 00:27:12,340
I bought it to start a new business,

349
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:14,600
but the technology was subpar,

350
00:27:15,910 --> 00:27:19,480
and the company had
no real business value.

351
00:27:21,210 --> 00:27:22,780
You could say...

352
00:27:23,510 --> 00:27:25,180
it was all style and no substance.

353
00:27:29,490 --> 00:27:32,560
I'm not so sure.
Based on my research,

354
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:35,090
the technology was
actually very advanced.

355
00:27:36,860 --> 00:27:40,730
That's because you don't know much
about biotech, Chloe.

356
00:27:41,870 --> 00:27:44,600
You just fell for Temi Bio's...

357
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:46,240
slick marketing.

358
00:27:48,170 --> 00:27:50,440
The CEO was a con man,

359
00:27:51,610 --> 00:27:54,080
an expert at embezzlement
and deception.

360
00:27:56,850 --> 00:27:59,080
He was irresponsible...

361
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:03,390
and cowardly, right to the very end.

362
00:28:11,530 --> 00:28:14,600
After brutally murdering my father,

363
00:28:15,430 --> 00:28:17,930
you call him a coward
and irresponsible?

364
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:23,240
Our bio division struggled for years
because of that mistake,

365
00:28:23,870 --> 00:28:27,780
but now we're giving it another shot
through rebranding.

366
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:31,950
Now that you're on board, Chloe,

367
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:36,320
I expect to see
some results this time.

368
00:28:42,090 --> 00:28:44,460
We should probably call it a wrap.

369
00:28:55,140 --> 00:28:56,270
In that case,

370
00:28:56,710 --> 00:28:59,040
could you give me the files
on Temi Bio?

371
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:22,830
I'd like to confirm for myself
whether what you're saying is true.

372
00:29:23,730 --> 00:29:26,500
I have a right to know...

373
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:31,710
if I was really that clueless
and just fell for the marketing.

374
00:29:34,410 --> 00:29:36,180
Temi Bio...

375
00:29:36,650 --> 00:29:38,280
is in the past.

376
00:29:39,350 --> 00:29:41,380
There's no need
to concern yourself...

377
00:29:42,220 --> 00:29:44,320
with outdated files.

378
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:47,920
It might not be the past.
It could be our history.

379
00:29:48,890 --> 00:29:52,330
Adele Group's bio division started
with Temi Bio.

380
00:29:53,260 --> 00:29:55,060
Shouldn't I get my facts straight?

381
00:30:08,010 --> 00:30:11,410
Chloe, why are you so obsessed
with Temi Bio?

382
00:30:24,260 --> 00:30:25,560
Here are the lab results.

383
00:30:31,940 --> 00:30:32,940
Chloe.

384
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:37,470
She's not really Baek Jin Ju,
is she?

385
00:31:19,620 --> 00:31:22,620
(Pearl in Red)

386
00:31:23,090 --> 00:31:25,720
Choi Yu Na took
the DNA test results and...

387
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:27,760
Hold on. You ran a paternity test?

388
00:31:27,820 --> 00:31:29,060
I requested a DNA test...

389
00:31:29,060 --> 00:31:31,060
and asked to have
the results expedited.

390
00:31:31,130 --> 00:31:33,100
Hold on. Keep an eye on her.

391
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:35,270
If this Chloe person is a problem,
just kick her out.

392
00:31:35,330 --> 00:31:37,530
That's what you're all
on my payroll for, isn't it?

393
00:31:37,630 --> 00:31:39,840
I heard Ms. Oh was making a scene
and screaming she'd kill someone.

394
00:31:39,840 --> 00:31:41,470
What is this about?

395
00:31:41,540 --> 00:31:43,210
What have you done now?

396
00:31:43,740 --> 00:31:44,740
Park Min Jun!

397
00:31:46,410 --> 00:31:48,410
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
